Project Synopsis & Features/File Structure/ Implementation of Main Files


PROJECT SYNOPSIS & Features : An andorid application which allows user to connect to flight gear application and 
                              set rudder, thorttle, aileron and elevator (and basicly fly the plane) with a controller.

File Structure :
            Joystick.java             |java|com.example.flightGearAndroidApp
            MainActivity.java         |java|com.example.flightGearAndroidApp
            Model.java                |java|com.example.flightGearAndroidApp
            ViewModel.java            |java|com.example.flightGearAndroidApp
            attr.xml                  |res|values
            
Implementation of Main Files:

                             attr.xml                         : decleration of joystick attributes. (x and y for locatin, and colors for joystick's parts) 
                              
                             Joystick.java                    : custom view class that implement the "onTouchEvent", convert view touching (joystick touching) into
                                                                aileron and elevator values.
                                                                
                             Model.java                       : contain all the logic - create connection with FG server, convert throttle and rudder seekbars 
                                                                values to the real throttle and ruuder values.
                              
                             ViewModel:                       : expose model fileds and use it logic
         
